<p data-start="880" data-end="952">You can copy/paste the HTML/JS I made for <strong data-start="922" data-end="934">Sitewize</strong> and it will work!</p>
<hr data-start="954" data-end="957">
<h3 data-start="959" data-end="1014">📱 Option 2: <strong data-start="976" data-end="1014">Use an App (if you prefer offline)</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1016" data-end="1050">If you want to edit files locally:</p>
<ul data-start="1052" data-end="1300">
<li data-start="1052" data-end="1196">
<p data-start="1054" data-end="1105">Install a <strong data-start="1064" data-end="1083">code editor app</strong> from AppGallery like:</p>
<ul data-start="1108" data-end="1196">
<li data-start="1108" data-end="1152">
<p data-start="1110" data-end="1152"><strong data-start="1110" data-end="1125">Spck Editor</strong> (lightweight, works great)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1155" data-end="1181">
<p data-start="1157" data-end="1181"><strong data-start="1157" data-end="1166">Acode</strong> (very popular)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1184" data-end="1196">
<p data-start="1186" data-end="1196"><strong data-start="1186" data-end="1196">Dcoder</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1197" data-end="1241">
<p data-start="1199" data-end="1241">Open your <code data-start="1209" data-end="1216">.html</code>, <code data-start="1218" data-end="1224">.css</code>, and <code data-start="1230" data-end="1235">.js</code> files</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1242" data-end="1300">
<p data-start="1244" data-end="1300">You can preview them in your browser by opening the file</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1302" data-end="1305">
<h3 data-start="1307" data-end="1347">🌍 Option 3: <strong data-start="1324" data-end="1347">Publish It Publicly</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1348" data-end="1409">Once your code is ready, you can make your site public using:</p>
<ul data-start="1411" data-end="1600">
<li data-start="1411" data-end="1470">
<p data-start="1413" data-end="1470"><a data-start="1413" data-end="1454" rel="noopener" target="_new" class="" href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub Pages</a> – Free and fast</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1471" data-end="1531">
<p data-start="1473" data-end="1531"><a data-start="1473" data-end="1503" rel="noopener" target="_new" class="" href="https://netlify.com/">Netlify</a> – Drag and drop your folder</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1532" data-end="1600">
<p data-start="1534" data-end="1600"><a data-start="1534" data-end="1562" rel="noopener" target="_new" class="" href="https://vercel.com/">Vercel</a> – Great for developers (needs GitHub)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1602" data-end="1652">I can walk you through <strong data-start="1625" data-end="1639">every step</strong> if you want.</p>

<hr data-start="557" data-end="560">
<h3 data-start="562" data-end="600">🔹 Step 2: Create a New Repository</h3>
<ol data-start="601" data-end="752">
<li data-start="601" data-end="660">
<p data-start="604" data-end="660">After logging in, tap ➕ top right → <strong data-start="640" data-end="660">"New repository"</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="661" data-end="697">
<p data-start="664" data-end="697">Name it something like <code data-start="687" data-end="697">sitewize</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="698" data-end="723">
<p data-start="701" data-end="723">✅ Check “Add a README”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="724" data-end="752">
<p data-start="727" data-end="752">Tap <strong data-start="731" data-end="752">Create repository</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="754" data-end="757">
<h3 data-start="759" data-end="799">🔹 Step 3: Upload Your Website Files</h3>
<ol data-start="800" data-end="1027">
<li data-start="800" data-end="822">
<p data-start="803" data-end="822">Go to your new repo</p>
</li>
<li data-start="823" data-end="861">
<p data-start="826" data-end="861">Tap <strong data-start="830" data-end="861">"Add file" → "Upload files"</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="862" data-end="992">
<p data-start="865" data-end="872">Upload:</p>
<ul data-start="876" data-end="992">
<li data-start="876" data-end="902">
<p data-start="878" data-end="902"><code data-start="878" data-end="890">index.html</code> (main page)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="906" data-end="928">
<p data-start="908" data-end="928"><code data-start="908" data-end="919">style.css</code> (design)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="932" data-end="963">
<p data-start="934" data-end="963"><code data-start="934" data-end="945">script.js</code> (if you have one)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="967" data-end="992">
<p data-start="969" data-end="992">any images, icons, etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="993" data-end="1027">
<p data-start="996" data-end="1027">Tap <strong data-start="1000" data-end="1018">Commit changes</strong> (bottom)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="1029" data-end="1032">
<h3 data-start="1034" data-end="1068">🔹 Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages</h3>
<ol data-start="1069" data-end="1189">
<li data-start="1069" data-end="1116">
<p data-start="1072" data-end="1116">In your repo, go to <strong data-start="1092" data-end="1104">Settings</strong> → <strong data-start="1107" data-end="1116">Pages</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1117" data-end="1173">
<p data-start="1120" data-end="1173">Under <strong data-start="1126" data-end="1138">"Source"</strong>, select <code data-start="1147" data-end="1153">main</code> branch → <code data-start="1163" data-end="1173">/ (root)</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1174" data-end="1189">
<p data-start="1177" data-end="1189">Tap <strong data-start="1181" data-end="1189">Save</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="1191" data-end="1210">Wait 10–30 seconds…</p>
<p data-start="1212" data-end="1238">Your site will be live at:</p>

<hr data-start="148" data-end="151">
<h3 data-start="153" data-end="197">✅ After creating your repo, follow this:</h3>
<ol data-start="199" data-end="648">
<li data-start="199" data-end="343">
<p data-start="202" data-end="343"><strong data-start="202" data-end="223">Open your browser</strong> and go to:<br data-start="234" data-end="237">

(replace <code data-start="301" data-end="316">YOUR_USERNAME</code> with your GitHub username)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="345" data-end="399">
<p data-start="348" data-end="399">Now look for the section with your <strong data-start="383" data-end="398">README file</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="401" data-end="494">
<p data-start="404" data-end="494">Near the top-right, you will see a grey button that says:<br data-start="461" data-end="464">
🟦 <strong data-start="470" data-end="484">"Add file"</strong> — Tap it.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="496" data-end="537">
<p data-start="499" data-end="537">Then choose:<br data-start="511" data-end="514">
✅ <strong data-start="519" data-end="537">"Upload files"</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="539" data-end="648">
<p data-start="542" data-end="596">Now upload the contents of the <code data-start="573" data-end="579">.zip</code> file I gave you:</p>
<ul data-start="600" data-end="648">
<li data-start="600" data-end="614">
<p data-start="602" data-end="614"><code data-start="602" data-end="614">index.html</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="618" data-end="631">
<p data-start="620" data-end="631"><code data-start="620" data-end="631">style.css</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="635" data-end="648">
<p data-start="637" data-end="648"><code data-start="637" data-end="648">script.js</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="650" data-end="722">⚠️ Don’t upload the whole ZIP — open it and upload the <strong data-start="705" data-end="721">files inside</strong>.</p>
<ol start="6" data-start="724" data-end="776">
<li data-start="724" data-end="776">
<p data-start="727" data-end="776">Scroll down and tap:<br data-start="747" data-end="750">

</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="778" data-end="781">
<h3 data-start="783" data-end="823">👀 Can’t find the “Add file” button?</h3>
<p data-start="824" data-end="975">It might be hidden in mobile view. Tap the <strong data-start="867" data-end="885">three dots (⋯)</strong> at the top right or <strong data-start="906" data-end="941">rotate your device to landscape</strong>. It may also be under a dropdown.</p>

<hr data-start="105" data-end="108">
<h2 data-start="110" data-end="166">✅ Step-by-Step Guide to Upload Your Website to GitHub</h2>
<h3 data-start="168" data-end="209">✅ STEP 1: Open Your GitHub Repository</h3>
<p data-start="210" data-end="328">Go to:<br data-start="216" data-end="219">
👉 <code data-start="222" data-end="265">https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/sitewize</code><br data-start="265" data-end="268">
<em data-start="268" data-end="328">(Replace <code data-start="278" data-end="293">YOUR_USERNAME</code> with your actual GitHub username)</em></p>
<hr data-start="330" data-end="333">
<h3 data-start="335" data-end="382">✅ STEP 2: Click “Add File” → “Upload Files”</h3>
<ol data-start="383" data-end="468">
<li data-start="383" data-end="439">
<p data-start="386" data-end="439">Click the <strong data-start="396" data-end="410">“Add file”</strong> dropdown near the top-right.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="440" data-end="468">
<p data-start="443" data-end="468">Choose <strong data-start="450" data-end="468">“Upload files”</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
&lt;img src="https://docs.github.com/assets/images/help/repository/code-tab-add-file-button.png" width="400"/&gt;
<hr data-start="579" data-end="582">
<h3 data-start="584" data-end="615">✅ STEP 3: Upload Your Files</h3>
<ol data-start="616" data-end="801">
<li data-start="616" data-end="687">
<p data-start="619" data-end="687">Open the <code data-start="628" data-end="634">.zip</code> file I gave you (named <code data-start="658" data-end="686">Sitewize_Website_Files.zip</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="688" data-end="801">
<p data-start="691" data-end="749">Drag and drop <strong data-start="705" data-end="720">these files</strong> into the GitHub upload area:</p>
<ul data-start="753" data-end="801">
<li data-start="753" data-end="767">
<p data-start="755" data-end="767"><code data-start="755" data-end="767">index.html</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="771" data-end="784">
<p data-start="773" data-end="784"><code data-start="773" data-end="784">style.css</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="788" data-end="801">
<p data-start="790" data-end="801"><code data-start="790" data-end="801">script.js</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="803" data-end="875">❗️<strong data-start="805" data-end="840">Do NOT upload the <code data-start="825" data-end="831">.zip</code> itself</strong> — only upload the files inside it.</p>
<hr data-start="877" data-end="880">
<h3 data-start="882" data-end="918">✅ STEP 4: Click “Commit changes”</h3>
<ol data-start="919" data-end="990">
<li data-start="919" data-end="933">
<p data-start="922" data-end="933">Scroll down</p>
</li>
<li data-start="934" data-end="990">
<p data-start="937" data-end="990">Click the green ✅ <strong data-start="955" data-end="975">“Commit changes”</strong> button to save</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="992" data-end="995">
<p data-start="997" data-end="1053">Now you’ve uploaded your files. Time for the final step:</p>
<hr data-start="1055" data-end="1058">
<h2 data-start="1060" data-end="1114">🚀 STEP 5: Turn On GitHub Pages (Make Website Live)</h2>
<ol data-start="1115" data-end="1405">
<li data-start="1115" data-end="1210">
<p data-start="1118" data-end="1210">Click on <strong data-start="1127" data-end="1141">“Settings”</strong> tab in your repo<br data-start="1158" data-end="1161">
(Top right, next to “Insights” and “Security”)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1212" data-end="1268">
<p data-start="1215" data-end="1268">Scroll down on the left sidebar and click <strong data-start="1257" data-end="1268">“Pages”</strong></p>

class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light"><p data-start="0" data-end="109">Great — let's go <strong data-start="17" data-end="48">step-by-step on your laptop</strong> to help you find <strong data-start="66" data-end="84">“Upload files”</strong> inside your GitHub repo:</p>
<hr data-start="111" data-end="114">
<h2 data-start="116" data-end="173">✅ Where to Find “Upload Files” on GitHub (Laptop View)</h2>
<h3 data-start="175" data-end="206">🔹 Step 1: Open Your Repo</h3>
<p data-start="207" data-end="323">Go to:<br data-start="213" data-end="216">
👉 <code data-start="219" data-end="262">https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/sitewize</code><br data-start="262" data-end="265">
(Replace <code data-start="274" data-end="289">YOUR_USERNAME</code> with your actual GitHub username)</p>
<hr data-start="325" data-end="328">
<h3 data-start="330" data-end="373">🔹 Step 2: Find the “Add file” Button</h3>
<p data-start="374" data-end="433">At the <strong data-start="381" data-end="394">top right</strong>, just above the file list, you'll see:</p>
<p data-start="435" data-end="473">🟦 <strong data-start="438" data-end="450">Add file</strong> ▼ (with a small arrow)</p>
<hr data-start="475" data-end="478">
<h3 data-start="480" data-end="521">🔹 Step 3: Click <strong data-start="501" data-end="519">“Upload files”</strong></h3>
<p data-start="522" data-end="567">Click the arrow ▼ and a dropdown will appear.</p>
<p data-start="569" data-end="614">🟩 From the dropdown, choose <strong data-start="598" data-end="614">Upload files</strong></p>
<blockquote data-start="616" data-end="712">
<p data-start="618" data-end="712">✅ This will take you to a page where you can drag and drop files or browse from your computer.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="714" data-end="717">
<h3 data-start="719" data-end="760">🔹 Step 4: Drag and Drop Your Files</h3>
<ol data-start="761" data-end="896">
<li data-start="761" data-end="797">
<p data-start="764" data-end="797">Open the <code data-start="773" data-end="779">.zip</code> file I gave you</p>
</li>
<li data-start="798" data-end="896">
<p data-start="801" data-end="844">Drag these files into GitHub’s upload area:</p>
<ul data-start="848" data-end="896">
<li data-start="848" data-end="862">
<p data-start="850" data-end="862"><code data-start="850" data-end="862">index.html</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="866" data-end="879">
<p data-start="868" data-end="879"><code data-start="868" data-end="879">style.css</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="883" data-end="896">
<p data-start="885" data-end="896"><code data-start="885" data-end="896">script.js</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<blockquote data-start="898" data-end="960">
<p data-start="900" data-end="960">❌ Don’t upload the <code data-start="919" data-end="925">.zip</code> itself — only the files inside it!</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="962" data-end="965">
<h3 data-start="967" data-end="1024">🔹 Step 5: Scroll Down &amp; Click <strong data-start="1002" data-end="1022">“Commit changes”</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1025" data-end="1074">✅ This will save your files into the GitHub repo.</p>

<hr data-start="94" data-end="97">
<h3 data-start="99" data-end="159">🗑️ How to Delete Files from GitHub Repo (Website Files)</h3>
<h4 data-start="161" data-end="203">✅ If you're using the GitHub website:</h4>
<ol data-start="205" data-end="645">
<li data-start="205" data-end="294">
<p data-start="208" data-end="294">Go to your repository on GitHub (example: <code data-start="250" data-end="293">https://github.com/your-username/sitewize</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="295" data-end="369">
<p data-start="298" data-end="369">Find the file you want to delete (like <code data-start="337" data-end="349">index.html</code>, <code data-start="351" data-end="362">style.css</code>, etc.)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="370" data-end="407">
<p data-start="373" data-end="407">Click the <strong data-start="383" data-end="396">file name</strong> to open it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="408" data-end="474">
<p data-start="411" data-end="474">Click the <strong data-start="421" data-end="457">🖊️ pencil icon (Edit this file)</strong> at the top right</p>
</li>
<li data-start="475" data-end="541">
<p data-start="478" data-end="541">Scroll down and click <strong data-start="500" data-end="522">"Delete this file"</strong> (below the editor)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="542" data-end="615">
<p data-start="545" data-end="615">In the commit message box, type something like:<br data-start="592" data-end="595">
<code data-start="598" data-end="615">Delete old file</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="616" data-end="645">
<p data-start="619" data-end="645">Click <strong data-start="625" data-end="645">“Commit changes”</strong></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="647" data-end="687">Repeat for each file you want to remove.</p>
<hr data-start="689" data-end="692">
<h3 data-start="694" data-end="709">💡 Pro Tip:</h3>
<p data-start="710" data-end="763">After deleting old files, upload your new ones using:</p>
<ul data-start="765" data-end="811">
<li data-start="765" data-end="811">
<p data-start="767" data-end="811"><strong data-start="767" data-end="811">Add file → Upload files → Commit changes</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>

language-markdown"><span><span><span class="hljs-section"># Sitewize – Smart Website Safety Extension</span></span><span>

Sitewize is a browser extension that helps you browse safely by detecting and alerting you to:
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> 🟢 Safe websites
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> 🟡 Suspicious websites
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> 🔴 Dangerous or scam websites

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 🌟 Features</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Real-time website scanning
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Color-coded safety alerts
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Popup customization
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Whitelist management
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Malicious site blocking

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 📦 How to Install the Extension</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">1.</span></span><span> Download the extension ZIP
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">2.</span></span><span> Unzip it to a folder
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">3.</span></span><span> Open Chrome and go to </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`chrome://extensions`</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">4.</span></span><span> Enable </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Developer Mode**</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">5.</span></span><span> Click </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Load unpacked**</span></span><span> and select the folder

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## 📞 Contact</span></span><span>
WhatsApp: 0566199422
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
